				\begin{document}$$E=E^0-\frac{nF}{2RT}\hbox{lnQ}.$$\end{document}where E is the measured electrochemical potential (V), E0 represents the standard electrode potential, R is the universal gas constant (8.314 J/mol·K), T denotes the body temperature (310.15 K), n is the number of electrons transferred in the redox reaction, F represents Faraday’s constant (96,485 C/mol), and Q refers to the reaction quotient, which corresponds to biomarker concentration in the biological sample.
